SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 436
By Briggs
A RESOLUTION to recognize Terry Carroll of the Tennessee
State Employees Association on the occasion of
his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of industry; and
WHEREAS, Terry Carroll is one such estimable person who served with distinction as
the Deputy Executive Director of the Tennessee State Employees Association (TSEA) and took
his much-deserved retirement on December 31, 2023; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll began his illustrious career with TSEA on August 24, 1992,
serving as the West Tennessee Field Representative for the organization, a post he held until
January 1995; and
WHEREAS, in 1995, he was named Middle Tennessee Field Representative and held
that position for the next twenty years before being named the Employee Compensation and
Benefits Coordinator in September 2015; and
WHEREAS, in January 2019, Mr. Carroll was named Government Affairs Director for
TSEA, in which capacity he displayed his dedication to state employees and his unwavering
belief in their work and in TSEA's mission; and
WHEREAS, during his years with TSEA, he won the respect and admiration of state
employees across the State of Tennessee, who appreciated his visionary leadership on behalf
of all TSEA members; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll demonstrated his commitment to TSEA by continuing to lend his
time and talents to the organization's representatives at the State Capitol for nearly a year after
taking his retirement; and
