WHEREAS, Terry Carroll is an active and important part of his community and served as
the judge's chair for the Miss Austin Peay and Miss Queen City pageants in Clarksville, ensuring
that the judges experienced Southern hospitality during the events; and
WHEREAS, hailing from beautiful West Tennessee, Mr. Carroll grew up following the
Miss Tennessee pageant in Jackson, and his knowledge of talent winners and those crowned
Miss Tennessee is legendary; and
WHEREAS, he is enjoying his retirement by pursuing his love of travel, having visited
the United Kingdom, France, Italy, Austria, the Slovak Republic, Aruba, Canada, Germany,
Belgium, Scotland, and France; and
WHEREAS, Terry Carroll exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, Terry Carroll demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of his
colleagues and the members of the Tennessee State Employees Association; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we extend to Terry Carroll our heartfelt wishes for a
happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
